Beyonce Knowles is an American singer, songwriter, and actress born in 1981 in Texas. She started her career in the 1990s as part of the girl group Destiny's Child, which went on to significant commercial success. In 2003, Beyonce launched her solo career with the release of her debut album Dangerously in Love, which won a Grammy for best R&B album. Along with her successful music career, Beyonce has also found success as an actress appearing in films such as Austin Powers and Dreamgirls. Beyond music and film, she has also pursued other business ventures including fashion design and endorsement deals.
